# Plan: Professional Animated Landing Page + UI Polish

## Context
The app is a React + Vite + Tailwind + framer-motion HR/payroll system with a consistent
neo-brutalist design system (lime `--primary #C9FF3D`, hard offset shadows `--shadow`,
sharp radii, dark background). Currently `/` redirects straight to `/login` — there is no
public landing/marketing page. `framer-motion` is already installed.

Goal: add a professional, animated landing page shown BEFORE login that showcases features
one-by-one with cool sliding animations, plus a few polish improvements that make the whole
app look more professional — all while staying consistent with the existing design tokens.

## Steps

### 1. Create animated Landing page
- New file: `frontend/src/pages/LandingPage.jsx`
- A full-screen, scroll-driven marketing page built with `framer-motion` (`motion`, `useScroll`,
  `useTransform`, `AnimatePresence`):
  - **Hero**: big headline "Enterprise HRMS", animated gradient/dotted background, CTA buttons
    ("Get Started" -> /login, "Watch Demo"). Staggered entrance.
  - **Feature showcase**: features revealed one-by-one with sliding/scroll animations as the
    user scrolls (payroll, attendance, leaves, documents, notices). Each feature slides in from
    alternating sides with the neo-brutalist card style (border-strong + offset shadow).
  - **Stats band**: animated count-up numbers (employees managed, payroll processed, etc.).
  - **How it works / steps** section with sliding steps.
  - **Testimonial / CTA** section.
  - **Footer** with brand.
- Use existing CSS variables (var(--primary), var(--surface), var(--shadow), var(--border-strong),
  var(--radius)) so it matches the app. Add a small landing-specific stylesheet block in global.css.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

### 2. Route the landing page
- In `frontend/src/App.jsx`: change `/` to render `<LandingPage />` instead of redirecting to
  `/login`. Keep `/login` and other routes intact. Landing "Sign In" button navigates to /login.

### 3. UI polish improvements (consistent with design system)
- Add reusable landing styles to `frontend/src/styles/global.css`: `.landing-*`, animated
  background grid, gradient text utility, scroll-reveal helpers.
- Improve the Login page slightly: give it the same polished hero/feature vibe by adding a
  side brand panel (split-screen) so it no longer feels bare. Keep it functional.
- Add subtle scroll-reveal wrapper component `frontend/src/components/Reveal.jsx` (motion-based)
  for reuse across pages.

## Files
- Add: `frontend/src/pages/LandingPage.jsx`
- Add: `frontend/src/components/Reveal.jsx`
- Edit: `frontend/src/App.jsx` (route `/`)
- Edit: `frontend/src/styles/global.css` (landing styles + background)
- Edit: `frontend/src/pages/LoginPage.jsx` (split-screen brand panel) — optional polish

## Verification
- `cd frontend && npm run build` to ensure it compiles.
- `npm run dev` and visually confirm landing page animations and that /login still works.
